<div class="reflist " style=" list-style-type: decimal;" about="#mwt1453" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"Reflist","href":"./Template:Reflist"},"params":{"group":{"wt":"note"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwBcc">
<div class="mw-references-wrap" typeof="mw:Extension/references" about="#mwt3238" data-mw='{"name":"references","attrs":{"group":"note","responsive":"1"},"body":{"html":""}}'><ol class="mw-references references" data-mw-group="note"><li about="#cite_note-1" id="cite_note-1"><a href="./Islam#cite_ref-1" data-mw-group="note" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-1" class="mw-reference-text">There are ten pronunciations of <i id="mwBcg">Islam</i> in English, differing in whether the first or second syllable has the stress, whether the <i id="mwBck">s</i> is <span class="IPA nowrap" title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" about="#mwt18" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"IPAslink","href":"./Template:IPAslink"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"z"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwBco">/<a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Voiced_alveolar_sibilant" title="Voiced alveolar sibilant" id="mwBcs" class="mw-redirect">z</a>/</span> or <span class="IPA nowrap" title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" about="#mwt19" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"IPAslink","href":"./Template:IPAslink"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"s"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwBcw">/<a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Voiceless_alveolar_sibilant" title="Voiceless alveolar sibilant" id="mwBc0" class="mw-redirect">s</a>/</span>, and whether the <i id="mwBc4">a</i> is pronounced <span class="IPA nowrap" title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" about="#mwt20" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"IPAslink","href":"./Template:IPAslink"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"ɑː"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwBc8">/<a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Open_back_unrounded_vowel" title="Open back unrounded vowel" id="mwBdA">ɑː</a>/</span>, <span class="IPA nowrap" title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" about="#mwt21" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"IPAslink","href":"./Template:IPAslink"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"æ"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwBdE">/<a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Near-open_front_unrounded_vowel" title="Near-open front unrounded vowel" id="mwBdI">æ</a>/</span> or (when the stress is on the first syllable) <span class="IPA nowrap" title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" about="#mwt22" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"IPAslink","href":"./Template:IPAslink"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"ə"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwBdM">/<a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Mid_central_vowel" title="Mid central vowel" id="mwBdQ">ə</a>/</span> (Merriam Webster). The most common are <span class="nowrap" about="#mwt23" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"IPAc-en","href":"./Template:IPAc-en"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"ˈ"},"2":{"wt":"ɪ"},"3":{"wt":"z"},"4":{"wt":"l"},"5":{"wt":"əm"},"6":{"wt":",_"},"7":{"wt":"ˈ"},"8":{"wt":"ɪ"},"9":{"wt":"s"},"10":{"wt":"l"},"11":{"wt":"əm"},"12":{"wt":",_"},"13":{"wt":"ɪ"},"14":{"wt":"z"},"15":{"wt":"ˈ"},"16":{"wt":"l"},"17":{"wt":"ɑː"},"18":{"wt":"m"},"19":{"wt":",_"},"20":{"wt":"ɪ"},"21":{"wt":"s"},"22":{"wt":"&apos;"},"23":{"wt":"l"},"24":{"wt":"ɑː"},"25":{"wt":"m"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwBdU"><span class="IPA nopopups noexcerpt" id="mwBdY"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Help:IPA/English" title="Help:IPA/English" id="mwBdc">/<span style="border-bottom:1px dotted" id="mwBdg"><span title="/ˈ/: primary stress follows" id="mwBdk">ˈ</span><span title="/ɪ/: 'i' in 'kit'" id="mwBdo">ɪ</span><span title="'z' in 'zoom'" id="mwBds">z</span><span title="'l' in 'lie'" id="mwBdw">l</span><span title="/əm/: 'm' in 'rhythm'" id="mwBd0">əm</span></span>, <wbr id="mwBd4"/><span style="border-bottom:1px dotted" id="mwBd8"><span title="/ˈ/: primary stress follows" id="mwBeA">ˈ</span><span title="/ɪ/: 'i' in 'kit'" id="mwBeE">ɪ</span><span title="'s' in 'sigh'" id="mwBeI">s</span><span 