wBrA"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt75" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwBrE"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-27" id="cite_note-27"><a href="./Islam#cite_ref-27" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-27" class="mw-reference-text">The preaching of Islam: a history of the propagation of the Muslim faith By Sir Thomas Walker Arnold, pp. 125–258</span></li><li about="#cite_note-Sunni-eb-28" id="cite_note-Sunni-eb-28"><span rel="mw:referencedBy"><a href="./Islam#cite_ref-Sunni-eb_28-0"><span class="mw-linkback-text">1 </span></a><a href="./Islam#cite_ref-Sunni-eb_28-1"><span class="mw-linkback-text">2 </span></a></span> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-Sunni-eb-28" class="mw-reference-text">
