<li id="mwBsk"><cite class="citation web" about="#mwt1117" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite web","href":"./Template:Cite_web"},"params":{"url":{"wt":"https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/fields/2122.html"},"title":{"wt":"Religions"},"accessdate":{"wt":"2010-08-25"},"website":{"wt":"[[The World Factbook]]"},"publisher":{"wt":"Central Intelligence Agency"},"quote":{"wt":"Sunni Islam accounts for over 75% of the world&apos;s Muslim population..."}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwBso"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/fields/2122.html" id="mwBss">"Religions"</a>. <i id="mwBsw"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./The_World_Factbook" title="The World Factbook" id="mwBs0">The World Factbook</a></i>. Central Intelligence Agency<span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwBs4">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwBs8">2010-08-25</span></span>. <q id="mwBtA">Sunni Islam accounts for over 75% of the world's Muslim population...</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=The+World+Factbook&amp;rft.atitle=Religions&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cia.gov%2Flibrary%2Fpublications%2Fthe-world-factbook%2Ffields%2F2122.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIslam" class="Z3988" about="#mwt1117" id="mwBtE"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt1117" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwBtI"/></li></ul></span></li><li about="#cite_note-Shia-29" id="cite_note-Shia-29"><span rel="mw:referencedBy"><a href="./Islam#cite_ref-Shia_29-0"><span class="mw-linkback-text">1 </span></a><a href="./Islam#cite_ref-Shia_29-1"><span class="mw-linkback-text">2 </span></a></span> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-Shia-29" class="mw-reference-text">See
<ul id="mwBtM"><li id="mwBtQ"><cite class="citation web" about="#mwt1161" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite web","href":"./Template:Cite_web"},"params":{"url":{"wt":"http://www.pewforum.org/2009/10/07/mapping-the-global-muslim-population/"},"title":{"wt":"Mapping the Global Muslim Population: A Report on the Size and Distribution of the World&apos;s Muslim Population"},"date":{"wt":"2009-10-07"},"accessdate":{"wt":"2013-09-24"},"website":{"wt":"Pew Research Center"},"quote":{"wt":"The Pew Forum&apos;s estimate of the Shia population (10–13%) is in keeping with previous estimates, which generally have been in the range of 10–15%. Some previous estimates, however, have placed the number of Shias at nearly 20% of the world&apos;s Muslim population."}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwBtU"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.pewforum.org/2009/10/07/mapping-the-global-muslim-population/" id="mwBtY">"Mapping the Global Muslim Population: A Report on the Size and Distribution of the World's Muslim Population"</a>. <i id="mwBtc">Pew Research Center</i>. 2009-10-07<span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwBtg">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwBtk">2013-09-24</span></span>. <q id="mwBto">The Pew Forum's estimate of the Shia population (10–13%) is in keeping with previous estimates, which generally have been in the range of 10–15%. Some previous estimates, however, have placed the number of Shias at nearly 20% of the world's Muslim population.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Pew+Research+Center&amp;rft.atitle=Mapping+the+Global+Muslim+Population%3A+A+Report+on+the+Size+and+Distribution+of+the+World%27s+Muslim+Population&amp;rft.date=2009-10-07&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewforum.org%2F2009%2F10%2F07%2Fmapping-the-global-muslim-population%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIslam" class="Z3988" about="#mwt1161"